{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f035be05-3b6f-4ed1-8ce6-e2852fbd859e","content":"Here are the most common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (`dotnet new`)**\n- `webapi` — minimal API or controller-based\n- Auth options: `--auth Individual` (Identity/JWT), `--auth IndividualB2C` (Azure AD B2C), `--auth SingleOrg` (Azure AD), `--auth Windows`\n\n**Node.js / Express**\n- Use `express-generator` or scaffold manually\n- Auth: Passport.js (JWT, OAuth2, local), express-jwt, Auth0 SDK\n\n**Python / FastAPI**\n- `fastapi` with `python-jose` for JWT, or `authlib` for OAuth2\n\n**Java / Spring Boot**\n- Use Spring Initializr (`start.spring.io`) with **Spring Security** dependency\n- Auth: JWT, OAuth2 Resource Server, Basic Auth\n\nFor a quick start with .NET, for example:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -n MyApi\n```\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a specific project for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ee80d2b2-d13c-4f22-b368-2e2556204fbf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most common options.","outputTokens":309,"requestId":"4024:2211CA:437F5C:4F06EC:69F0048B"},"id":"f671f8d6-eaf4-4b56-bead-e3d1b6173fe0","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:51:33.869Z","parentId":"6dedeb9f-af86-4aa6-9421-62060bce1061"}
